The register:
General purpose registers: in the CPU, each core can have its own general purpose registers, which is it own storage space which is extremely fast. When doing certain task, the cpu will try to put data in there
instead of memory because it a lot faster for cpu to access data in register when compare to memory. If the data is too large to fit in a register, a register will hold a pointer to the data so it can be accessed.









